summary: An Ordinance appropriating the sum of Five Thousand, Three Hundred and 86/100 Dollars ($5,300.86) from the Water Fund of the City of Seattle, to aid in the improvement of Twenty-fifth Avenue North, et al, authorized by Ordinance No. 16905, and repealing Ordinance No. 19329, entitled "An Ordinance appropriating the sum of Six Thousand Dollars ($6000.00), or so much thereof as may be necessary, from the Water Fund, to aid in the improvement of Twenty-fifth Avenue North et al, authorized by Ordinance No. 16905", approved October 19, 1908.
